# ReviewPulse v2 — Cursor rules (condensed)

The full “Feature Bible” lists 40+ capabilities (AI heatmaps, WhatsApp bots, benchmarks, API, badges, etc.). Implement **one vertical slice at a time** behind plan gates and tests—do not land half-finished surface area.

## Stack

Next.js App Router, MongoDB/Mongoose, NextAuth (Google + `business.manage` scope), Razorpay, Twilio WhatsApp, Tailwind, shadcn-style UI.

## Security and data

1. **Auth first** (`requireAuth` / session), **plan gate second**, **queries scoped to `userId`** (or agency owner rules where applicable).
2. Validate inputs with **Zod**; return structured errors; never leak stack traces or raw provider errors to the client.
3. **PII**: healthcare / clinic modes must never echo patient details in AI replies when enabled (see bible D2).

## WhatsApp / Twilio

- Max message length **1024** characters; interactive button titles **≤ 20** chars.
- **Alerts** (automated sends from review sync): Starter+ only; cap daily volume (existing `MAX_WHATSAPP_ALERTS_PER_DAY`).
- **Test ping** (`/api/user/whatsapp/test`): allowed on **any** plan when Twilio env is set and a valid **saved** E.164 number exists.
- Normalize Indian mobiles to `+91…` on save (`lib/phone-e164.ts`).
- Production webhooks: set `TWILIO_WEBHOOK_PUBLIC_URL` so signature validation matches the public URL.

## Google / locations

- Prefer **`GET /locations/connect`**, which calls `signIn('google', { redirectTo: '/locations' })`, over linking directly to `/api/auth/signin/google` so the OAuth flow matches NextAuth v5 and reliably re-runs the sign-in callback (token refresh + `provisionLocationsFromGoogleOAuth`).

## Performance

- Avoid `force-dynamic` on entire dashboard layout unless required.
- Prefer **Mongo aggregations** for analytics; cache expensive rollups on `Location` or dedicated summary collections when the bible calls for heatmaps / velocity / benchmarks.
- Do **not** block page loads on OpenAI—use cron, `revalidatePath`, or background jobs.

## OpenAI cost

- Default model **`gpt-4o-mini`**; token ceilings: replies ~500, insights ~300, classifications ~150; batch classify when possible.

## Agency

- Runtime workspace and `/api/agency/bootstrap` require **`plan === 'agency'`**.
- Custom host branding: `AGENCY_HOST_MAP` in production; middleware must keep running on `/` so mapped hosts still receive `x-agency-id`.

## When adding a bible feature

Add model fields + indexes (especially `userId`, dates used in filters), UI behind the correct **plan** tier, API route with auth + Zod, and a short regression path (manual or automated).
